  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><strong>Acid Spray.</strong></em> As an action, you can violently expel acid in a 15-foot cone. When you do so, each creature in the area of the exhalation must make a Wisdom saving throw (DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Constitution modifier). A creature takes 2d6 acid damage on a failed save, and half as much damage on a successful one. The damage increases to 4d6 at 5th level, 6d6 at 11th level, and 8d6 at 17th level. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus. You regain all expended uses when you complete a long rest.</p>",
